---
title: "Figure 1 — loop.sh Main Scheduler State Machine (single tick · drawn by Claude · 2026-04-26)"
---
flowchart TD
    Start([External tmux wrapper<br/>Recommended: while true; do bash loop.sh; sleep 300; done<br/>NOTE: 5-min cadence is external — loop.sh itself does not enforce it]) --> Tick[loop.sh tick begins]
    Tick --> Src[Source state/.consensus.env<br/>+ state/.crossval.env]

    Src --> G1{AUTORES_HOST_TAG<br/>exported?}
    G1 -- no --> X0[Refuse tick / exit 0]
    G1 -- yes --> G2{state/.loop.enabled.TAG<br/>sentinel exists?}
    G2 -- no --> X0
    G2 -- yes --> G3[Acquire flock on<br/>/tmp/autores.LOCK fd 9]
    G3 -- busy --> X0
    G3 -- got lock --> S0

    S0[Step 0 · sanity<br/>claude CLI / program.md / state.tsv exist]
    S0 --> S1

    S1[Step 1 · Reap<br/>scan rows where status=running]
    S1 --> R1{local /proc/PID alive?}
    R1 -- yes --> Rkeep[keep running]
    R1 -- no --> R2[read logs/exp_NNN_*.log<br/>tail+fstat to flush CIFS mtime]
    R2 --> R3{contains 'iter NNN FINISH rc=N'?}
    R3 -- rc=0 --> Rcomp[mark completed]
    R3 -- rc!=0 --> Rfail["WARN: mark **failed**<br/>**DEAD-END STATE**<br/>not auto-analyzed<br/>not git-committed<br/>NOT counted toward STOP rule<br/>requires manual intervention"]
    R3 -- no FINISH line --> R4{mtime age > 900s?}
    R4 -- yes --> Rcomp
    R4 -- no --> Rkeep

    Rkeep --> S2
    Rcomp --> S2
    Rfail --> S2

    S2{Step 2 · any row<br/>status=completed?}
    S2 -- yes --> ANALYZE[[See Figure 2:<br/>Analyze + async Consensus dispatch]]
    ANALYZE --> XA[exit 0<br/>blocks propose this tick]

    S2 -- no --> S3{Step 3 · STOP criteria<br/>NOTE: top-of-file comment says 50<br/>actual code is 80}
    S3 -- LAUNCHED >= 80 --> XS[STOP / exit 0]
    S3 -- last 5 verdict=Failure count >= 3 --> XS
    S3 -- best_h >= 45 --> XS
    S3 -- none hit --> S4

    S4{Step 4 · running count<br/>>= MAX_CONCURRENT?}
    S4 -- yes --> XW[exit 0 / wait]
    S4 -- no --> GATE

    GATE{Propose-Gate<br/>standalone block, not a Step}
    GATE -- AUTORES_CONSENSUS_ENABLED != 1 --> S5pre[pass through]
    GATE -- enabled --> GATE2[find LATEST_ANALYZED:<br/>max iter where status=analyzed<br/>AND verdict != Bug]
    GATE2 --> GATE3{consensus.final.md<br/>exists for that iter?}
    GATE3 -- no --> XG[Propose blocked / exit 0]
    GATE3 -- yes --> GATE4["WARN: gate ONLY checks file existence<br/>does NOT verify STATUS=CONSENSUS/OVERRIDE/PARSE_FAIL<br/>known design gap: corrupt final.md still passes"]
    GATE4 --> S5pre

    S5pre[Step 5 · GPU pre-check<br/>nvidia-smi pick most-free GPU<br/>free_mem >= 24GB<br/>skip AUTORES_SKIP_GPUS]
    S5pre -- no GPU --> XN[exit 0]
    S5pre -- FREE_GPU chosen --> S5

    S5["Step 5 · Propose<br/>WARN: FREE_GPU is **pre-check ONLY**<br/>NOT passed to run_experiment.sh<br/>training picks GPU independently"]
    S5 --> S5a{Consensus enabled?}
    S5a -- yes --> S5b["Read prev iter's consensus.final.md<br/>build CONSENSUS_HINT marked BINDING<br/>WARN: PARSE_FAIL content still concatenated<br/>but next-step usually falls back to primary §8"]
    S5a -- no --> S5c[no hint — free hypothesis pick]
    S5b --> S5d
    S5c --> S5d

    S5d[timeout 900s claude -p PROPOSE<br/>--max-turns 60<br/>reads program.md / CLAUDE.md /<br/>**ALL** iter logs / state.tsv]
    S5d --> S5e[Write configs/ablation_shm/*.yaml<br/>optionally edit src/hysyn_zsl/*.py<br/>call: bash run_experiment.sh CONFIG NEXT_ITER]
    S5e --> S5f[run_experiment.sh:<br/>own GPU selection + reservation<br/>+ OOM preflight<br/>nohup python3 train.py in background<br/>append state.tsv: status=running]
    S5f --> XP[exit 0]

    classDef warn fill:#fff4e6,stroke:#e67e22,stroke-width:2px,color:#000
    classDef ok fill:#e8f5e9,stroke:#2e7d32,color:#000
    classDef step fill:#e3f2fd,stroke:#1565c0,color:#000
    classDef gate fill:#f3e5f5,stroke:#7b1fa2,color:#000
    class Rfail,GATE4,S5,S5b warn
    class S0,S1,S2,S3,S4,S5pre,S5d,S5e,S5f step
    class GATE,GATE2,GATE3 gate
